---
import ContentPageHero from './ContentPageHero.astro';
---

<div class="grid gap-10">
    <ContentPageHero
        eyebrow="Foundations / Inspiration"
        title="Stay hungry. Stay foolish."
    />

    <section
        class="block max-w-[46rem] pt-1 after:block after:clear-both after:content-['']"
    >
        <p class="text-base leading-[1.8] text-[#564a3f]">
            I wasn't alive when the <a
                class="text-[#123c62] underline decoration-[rgba(18,60,98,0.18)] underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors duration-150 ease-out hover:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:outline-none"
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whole_Earth_Catalog?utm_source=galexc"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer">Whole Earth Catalog</a
            > was in print and I honestly had no idea what it was until a few years
            ago. For whatever reason, I am struck by its <a
                class="text-[#123c62] underline decoration-[rgba(18,60,98,0.18)] underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors duration-150 ease-out hover:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:outline-none"
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whole_Earth_Catalog#/media/File:WEC-69F-C.jpg"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer">ethos</a
            > (as I understand it) and I often remind myself to try staying hungry
            and foolish. In today's technical landscape, however, this can easily
            push you towards endless acceleration - so I try to hold this against
            the <a
                class="text-[#123c62] underline decoration-[rgba(18,60,98,0.18)] underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors duration-150 ease-out hover:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:outline-none"
                href="https://longnow.org?utm_source=galexc"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer">Long Now's</a
            > much longer view, and ask whether what I'm building will still matter
            in decades, not just this week. I'm not entirely what what will.
        </p>

        <figure
            class="relative my-7 mx-auto w-[min(56vw,15rem)] before:absolute before:left-0 before:-top-2 before:block before:h-px before:w-12 before:bg-[rgba(120,113,108,0.22)] before:content-[''] min-[900px]:float-right min-[900px]:my-7 min-[900px]:ml-9 min-[900px]:mr-0 min-[900px]:w-[min(34vw,16rem)]"
        >
            <button
                class="block w-full cursor-pointer overflow-hidden border border-[rgba(120,113,108,0.2)] bg-[rgba(255,252,247,0.3)] p-2 transition-[border-color,transform,background] duration-[220ms] ease-out hover:-translate-y-px hover:border-[rgba(21,74,122,0.24)] hover:bg-[rgba(255,252,247,0.44)] focus-visible:border-[rgba(21,74,122,0.28)] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-4 focus-visible:ring-[rgba(21,74,122,0.08)]"
                type="button"
                data-manifesto-lightbox-open
                aria-label="Expand Whole Earth Epilog image"
            >
                <img
                    class="block w-full"
                    src="/stay-hungry-stay-foolish.png"
                    alt="Stay hungry. Stay foolish. image from Gilman's framed Whole Earth Epilog"
                />
            </button>
            <figcaption
                class="mt-2 text-center font-mono text-[0.68rem] leading-[1.85] tracking-[0.14em] text-[#7a6d60] uppercase"
            >
                Exhibit 01 - An original copy of the Whole Earth Epilog in my
                office, which provides a meaningful reminder for me.
            </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <dialog class="manifesto-lightbox" data-manifesto-lightbox>
            <button
                class="manifesto-lightbox__close"
                type="button"
                data-manifesto-lightbox-close
                aria-label="Close expanded image"
            >
                ×
            </button>
            <img
                class="manifesto-lightbox__image"
                src="/stay-hungry-stay-foolish.png"
                alt="Stay hungry. Stay foolish. image from Gilman's framed Whole Earth Epilog"
            />
        </dialog>

        <script is:inline>
            (() => {
                const dialog = document.querySelector(
                    '[data-manifesto-lightbox]',
                );
                const openButton = document.querySelector(
                    '[data-manifesto-lightbox-open]',
                );
                const closeButton = document.querySelector(
                    '[data-manifesto-lightbox-close]',
                );

                if (!(dialog instanceof HTMLDialogElement)) return;

                openButton?.addEventListener('click', () => dialog.showModal());
                closeButton?.addEventListener('click', () => dialog.close());
                dialog.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
                    const rect = dialog.getBoundingClientRect();
                    const inside =
                        rect.top <= event.clientY &&
                        event.clientY <= rect.top + rect.height &&
                        rect.left <= event.clientX &&
                        event.clientX <= rect.left + rect.width;
                    if (!inside) dialog.close();
                });
            })();
        </script>

        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-[1.8] text-[#564a3f]">
            I've seen several incredible innovations in the last ~15 years of
            <a
                class="text-[#123c62] underline decoration-[rgba(18,60,98,0.18)] underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors duration-150 ease-out hover:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:outline-none"
                href="https://pressroom.gm.com/gmbx/us/en/pressroom/home/news.detail.html/Pages/news/us/en/2022/sep/0915-motorsports.html"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer">deploying machine learning</a
            >
            into <a
                class="text-[#123c62] underline decoration-[rgba(18,60,98,0.18)] underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors duration-150 ease-out hover:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:outline-none"
                href="https://rhoimpact.com"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer">professional-grade products</a
            >
            (Neural nets, anyone? Containers? Serverless compute?). That said, LLMs
            have unlocked a step-change in capability unlike anything I've personally
            experienced. As one should, I turn to my nerdy friends, mentors, colleagues
            and communities like <a
                class="text-[#123c62] underline decoration-[rgba(18,60,98,0.18)] underline-offset-[0.18em] transition-colors duration-150 ease-out hover:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:text-[#0f3150] focus-visible:outline-none"
                href="https://agentcribs.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer">Agent Cribs</a
            > to try navigating this wacky, ever-changing world.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-[1.8] text-[#564a3f]">
            A few months ago I had an incredible experience that changed the
            trajectory of my AI-journey. My friend, Kyle, had his AI, KyleOps,
            shared an overview of what they had been building. The level of
            clarity and depth across a complex, evolving system was unlike
            anything I had ever seen before. Trying to explain complex DevOps
            concepts and setups is seriously challenging even in the best of
            times...KyleOps cranked it out in just a few minutes with an
            extremely cogent, actionable, helpful summary. It was truly
            inspiring. The moment I saw it, I felt compelled to start building.
        </p>

        <section class="mt-8">
            <blockquote
                class="grid w-4/5 justify-items-center mx-auto my-2 pb-4 after:mt-2.5 after:block after:h-px after:w-[max(12rem,32%)] after:bg-[rgba(21,74,122,0.3)] after:content-['']"
            >
                <p
                    class="m-0 w-full max-w-none text-center text-[clamp(2rem,3.2vw,2.65rem)] leading-none text-[#2b241d] [text-wrap:pretty]"
                    style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;"
                >
                    I hope GalexC can be a spark for<br /><em>your</em>
                    personal AI.
                </p>
            </blockquote>
        </section>
    </section>
</div>
